main event: An unidentified object was observed between Skagway & Juneau, Alaska on 5 July 1956.
interesting points: The object moved at an estimated speed of 1,200 mph., The object was observed for approximately 1 minute., Its silhouette resembled an aircraft but lacked visible wings or a tail., There were conflicting reports about bumps that looked like engines but no wings were discerned., The report concludes insufficient data for definitive classification.
sighted object: silhouette of an unidentified flying object
